definitions.definition: A type of small open pie, or piece of pastry, now typically containing jelly (US) / jam (UK) or conserve, or sometimes other fillings (chocolate, custard, egg , butter , historically even meat or other savory fillings).
A melt ( block of wax for use in a tart burner ) .
